{
  "texts": [
    "In this section, we record (without proofs) the formulas for the Ricci curvature of an invariant metric on a twisted principal bundle, which follow from O'Neill's formulas for the curvature of a Riemannian submersion.",
    "The presentation is based on [BL23a] (see also [Bes87, Chpt. 9] or [NT18]Prop.",
    "8.1,), but contains some additional remarks that are new to this paper.",
    "Throughout this section, U will denote a local section of adM, Û the corresponding invariant vertical vector field on M. Since the fibres of adM have a natural Lie algebra structure, adU:= [U, •] ∈ Der(adM) will denote, as usual, the (fibrewise) adjoint representation.",
    "We will also write X, Y for vector fields on B, and X, Ȳ for their corresponding horizontal lifts to M.An invariant metric g on M is determined by a triple (g B, H, h) as per Proposition 2.14, and π: M → B is a Riemannian submersion."
  ]
}